A US diplomat has been arrested for allegedly brandishing a gun on a civilian after an accident in Nairobi.Two vehicles were involved in an accident on Lusaka Road on Sunday. No injuries were reported but there was a snarl up.The diplomat, whose identity was not revealed immediately, was driving a four-wheel drive car bearing US embassy registration numbers.He is said to have brandished the weapon before driving off when the other motorist sought an explanation from him.The vehicle, registration number 29CD701K, was circulated in the police communication channel before the diplomat was stopped on University Way by traffic personnel.Witnesses said he was arrested and disarmed, and then taken to Central police station for questioning.Police said the embassy employee was grilled on the accident and his alleged use of the gun, and that his Ceska pistol taken away for analysis. The vehicle was also taken to the station.Officials of KK Security, which protects the embassy, were at the station to help the diplomat get released on bail.An official at the embassy said they were offering consular assistance.OCPD Robinson Thuku earlier said the accident involved a diplomat and a Kenyan.Thuku told the Star there was no shoot-out but added: "Somebody was involved in an accident and when he was approached he drew a gun."He said he did not have more details.But the United States Embassy refuted claims its employee drew a gun causing panic after the accident."Contrary to some reports, at no time did the embassy employee pull or fire a weapon," the embassy wrote on Twitter.The organisation added that they were cooperating with authorities carrying out investigations on the minor accident.